<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code calls get_rq_param_unquoted_copy_z(&params->opaque, info->opaque) without passing the remaining buffer size or checking that unif_buf_used + params->opaque.value.len + 1 <= unif_buf_size. The routine likely performs a string copy and zero-termination (i.e. uses memcpy/strcpy-like operations). If unif_buf_used is larger than expected (for example if the prior get_rq_uname call wrote more bytes than anticipated or returned an incorrect size), then info->opaque will point into less-than-params->opaque.value.len+1 bytes of allocated space and the copy will write beyond the allocated buffer. This would result in out-of-bounds accesses by string-handling operations and thus violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

